<paragraph id="376A6251FFC62B1AA4B5FE2B9E65FDF0" blockId="23.[178,1086,380,542]" pageId="23" pageNumber="258">
C o m m e n t: The above female was collected in the locality illustrated in 
<figureCitation id="AFEE7ED4FFC62B1AA7ECFE2B9811FE2B" box="[1003,1080,432,454]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="18.[178,211,1419,1441]" captionTargetBox="[191,1072,794,1410]" captionTargetId="figure-243@18.[191,1072,749,1410]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Fig. 31: Type locality of Cephennium kerpense nov.sp., Euconnus kerpensis nov.sp., and Stenichnus kerpensis nov.sp. (sample number 12)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5416199" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5416199/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="258">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
, where the other four species of 
<taxonomicName id="F0D519D2FFC62B1AA5F4FE569EAEFE0D" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[499,647,461,483]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="258" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Scydmaeninae">Scydmaeninae</taxonomicName>
were found, too. This species is similar to, but presumably not conspecific with, 
<taxonomicName id="F0D519D2FFC62B1AA633FE709F80FDEF" authority="FRANZ, 1966" authorityName="FRANZ" authorityYear="1966" box="[564,937,491,513]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Euconnus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="258" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dodecanicus">
<emphasis id="05A1BE43FFC62B1AA633FE709F37FDEE" box="[564,798,491,512]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="258">Euconnus dodecanicus</emphasis>
FRANZ, 1966
</taxonomicName>
from Rhodos. Males are required to clarify its identity.
</paragraph>
